# Backend Models Module

## PURPOSE
Database schemas and data models.
Defines structure for user data, payments, and subscriptions.

## CONTAINS
- User.js: User account model
- Payment.js: Payment transaction model
- Subscription.js: Email subscription model

## USER MODEL SCHEMA
```
{
  email: String (unique, required)
  password: String (hashed, required)
  createdAt: Date
  hasPaid: Boolean (default: false)
  paymentDate: Date
  stripeCustomerId: String
  runCount: Number (default: 0)
}
```

## PAYMENT MODEL SCHEMA
```
{
  userId: ObjectId (ref: User)
  amount: Number (500 = $5.00)
  currency: String (default: 'usd')
  stripeSessionId: String
  stripePaymentIntentId: String
  status: String (pending, completed, failed)
  createdAt: Date
}
```

## SUBSCRIPTION MODEL SCHEMA
```
{
  userId: ObjectId (ref: User)
  senderName: String
  senderEmail: String
  subject: String
  unsubscribeLink: String
  provider: String (gmail, outlook, yahoo)
  scannedAt: Date
}
```

## REFERENCES
- Parent: /backend/.windsurf
- Root: /.windsurf
- Used by: /backend/routes/*

## RULES
- Use Mongoose for MongoDB or Sequelize for PostgreSQL
- Hash passwords with bcrypt before saving
- Index frequently queried fields
- Validate data at model level
- Use timestamps for all models
